article.headline: James Madison 68, George Mason 66
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Devon Moore scored seven points in the final 3:30 minutes to give James Madison a 68-66 win over George Mason on Saturday. George Mason (16-7, 9-4 Colonial Athletic Association) led 60-57 with 4:41 left to play, before Moore sparked a 11-6 James Madison run. James Madison's run began on a layup by Dazzmond Thornton, before Moore hit two free throws to give the Dukes (16-9, 8-5) a 61-60 lead with 3:30 remaining in the game. After two free throws by John Vaughan, Moore hit two more shots from the foul line, followed by a jumper and a free throw with 3 seconds remaining to seal the win. Moore finished the game with 11 points. The Dukes were led by Kyle Swanston's 19 points and Thornton, who added 13. John Vaughan scored 19 points and Darryl Monroe had 13 for the Patriots.
